We call for the cryptos. We call for things to turn around. Father, you don't need to use that.

01:46:44.795 --> 01:46:51.599
You could use whatever you want to. You have a million and one ways to get us a million dollars. You can do whatever you need to do.

01:46:51.600 --> 01:47:04.079
People say we try to limit God—it has to be through this cryptocurrency, or this pink currency, or this precious metal. And if you don't, Lord, you're limited.

01:47:04.080 --> 01:47:16.479
God, if you could pay the Lord Jesus's taxes with a coin coming out of a fish's mouth, how much more could you do it again today?

01:47:16.480 --> 01:47:26.178
How much more? If the Lord could pay his taxes out of a coin from a fish's mouth, how much more could you use an angel?

01:47:26.179 --> 01:47:33.505
How much more could you use even the neighbor's dog? Who knows?

01:47:33.506 --> 01:47:42.726
The neighbor's dog could dig it up out of the yard, an old ancient treasure, and set it on your porch.

01:47:42.727 --> 01:47:54.959
You'd go, "Where'd that come from? What is that? That's a diamond!"And the Lord says, "Surprise, surprise."God's a God of surprises.

01:47:54.960 --> 01:48:13.439
Why not be like Gomer Pyle? "Surprise, surprise!"You know, it's the way you want to be.

01:48:13.440 --> 01:48:36.869
Braden's laughing at me here. Well, hallelujah. We're so grateful for every one of you to be here today.

01:48:36.870 --> 01:48:47.039
Thank you for being here. We love y'all. I'm expecting the best is yet to come.

01:48:47.040 --> 01:48:58.759
I'll end it there. We'll be back again. Put a smile on your face and a song in your heart.

01:48:58.760 --> 01:49:13.439
I'm feeling so drunk, Braden. The glory is so heavy. I can just feel it.

01:49:13.440 --> 01:49:28.729
It's all over my stomach and my body. I feel like I've run and am moving in slow motion.

01:49:28.730 --> 01:49:38.399
It's absolutely incredible what it does to your flesh. I feel it in my blood.

01:49:38.400 --> 01:49:55.519
The glory comes on you. Thank you, Lord. I don't know if it goes through the camera or not, but I don't really care.

01:49:55.520 --> 01:50:26.319
I needed to pray strength today, Lord. I needed a fresh strength.

01:50:26.320 --> 01:51:08.839
Thank you. I'm not satisfied with this. I want more. Praise the Lord, y'all.

01:51:08.840 --> 01:51:22.060
Remember, put a smile on your face and a song in your heart. Jesus loves you so much and we love you. God bless you and we'll see you again. Bye-bye.

